{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771596414,"nonce":"5sRw5+Fx8YM8CmEdtWCckFlErQM=","title":"Insurance check should not be required for employee borrowers","message":"The insurance_checked validation on Borrower is unconditional -- it requires all borrower types to have their insurance verified on create and update. However, employees (Mitarbeitende) of the university are insured through the institution, so requiring personal insurance verification for them is incorrect.\n\nThe id_checked validation already has a student-only conditional:\n  validates :id_checked, ..., if: Proc.new{|u| u.student? }\n\nBut insurance_checked does not:\n  validates :insurance_checked, inclusion: { in: [true], ... }, on: [:create, :update]\n\nFix: Add a similar conditional so insurance_checked is only required for students, or adjust the logic to match the actual policy for employee borrowers.\n\nFile: app/models/borrower.rb, line 9","files":null}]}